"""
Quantum Chemistry Interface Module - Sterile Pipeline Architecture
===================================================================

Replaces buggy Gaussian execution module with a robust "Sterile Pipeline"
architecture to fix I/O freezes on WSL, prevent disk overflow, and ensure
syntax compliance.

Gaussian Execution Paths:
========================

This module provides TWO Gaussian execution paths with overlapping responsibilities:

1. Sterile Pipeline Architecture (run_gaussian_optimization):
   - Entry point: run_gaussian_optimization(atoms, charge, mult, output_dir, config, route)
   - Uses: LinuxSandbox -> GaussianRunner -> ResultHarvester
   - Checkpoint naming: input.chk (from input.gjf)
   - Harvested artifacts: final_output.chk, final_output.log, .fchk (via try_formchk)
   - Used by: Newer pipeline components (ConformerEngine, etc.)
   - Pros: Sandboxing, disk space management, error handling
   - Cons: Different naming convention from GaussianInterface

2. GaussianInterface Legacy Path:
   - Entry point: GaussianInterface.optimize(xyz_file, output_dir, config, method, basis, ...)
   - Uses: write_input_file() -> subprocess.run()
   - Checkpoint naming: {jobname}.chk (from jobname parameter)
   - Harvested artifacts: {jobname}.log, {jobname}.chk, .fchk (via try_formchk)
   - Used by: Legacy components (AnchorPhase, TSOptimizer)
   - Pros: Direct file naming control, flexible jobname handling
   - Cons: Less robust error handling

Naming Convention Notes:
========================

Both paths generate .fchk files via try_formchk(), but use different base names:
- Sterile: final_output.fchk (from input.chk)
- Legacy: {jobname}.fchk (from {jobname}.chk)

This inconsistency can cause S4 degradation if the wrong artifact path is expected.
Future refactoring should unify these paths or pick one canonical approach.

Classes:
- InputFactory: Creates sanitized Gaussian input files
- LogParser: Extracts final geometry from Gaussian logs
- LinuxSandbox: Context manager for safe execution environment
- GaussianRunner: Executes Gaussian calculations safely
- ResultHarvester: Collects and validates results
- run_gaussian_optimization: Main pipeline function
- GaussianInterface: Legacy wrapper (see above)

Author: QC Descriptors Team
Date: 2026-01-15
"""

